inconvenience /ˌɪnkənˈviːnjəns/

(inconveniencing,inconvenienced,inconveniences) 

1. N-VAR If someone or something causes inconvenience , they cause problems or difficulties. 不方便 

例： We apologize for any inconvenience caused during the repairs. 我们对在修理过程中所造成的任何不便表示歉意。 

2. V-T If someone inconveniences you, they cause problems or difficulties for you. 给…带来不便 

例： He promised to be quick so as not to inconvenience them any further. 他答应快一些，以免给他们带来更多不便。

